    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "AMERICAN\nAIRWAYS\nPASSENGER MAIL EXPRESS\nINERHEED\n230Y\n149\n6OGKHEED ORION (MAIL ONLY) ~ WASP ENGWE * CONTROLLABLE PE",
      "The Lockheed Orion was used on certain routes by American\nAirvays for \"mail and express at speeds of about 200 miles per\nhour. \" These planas were placed in scheduled service on October\n27, 1933 and remained until 1935 when they were replaced by DC-2's.\nThis aircraft was the first type with retractable landing\ngear operated by American Airways.\nSpan:\n42°10\"\nLength:\n27'6*\nHeight:\nWing Area:\n#ing Loading:\nGross Weight:\nEmpty Weight:\nPayload:\n1,170#\nCrew: 1\nPassengers:\nNone\n275 sq. ft.\n19/7\n8g. It.\n5,200#\nEngine: Pratt-Whitney Wasp (S101)\nTakeoff H.P.s 420\nPower Loading:\nsg. It.\nFuel Capacity:\nHigh Speed:\n204 mph\nCruising Speed:\n171 mph\nStall Speed:\n64 mph\nService Ceiling:\n19,800'\n• AA -\nPhoto #4142"
    ],
